# project

- project is set up and ready for development

# product
- project name is openpuffer @draft
- openpuffer is a turbopuffer-compatible vector and full-text search service @draft

# architecture
- deployable as a single static binary with no required sidecar services @draft
- server process holds no durable local state; all persistence uses S3-compatible object storage @draft
- horizontal scaling works by running multiple stateless instances against the same bucket @draft

# search
- supports approximate nearest-neighbor vector search over embedding attributes @draft
- supports BM25-style full-text search over text attributes @draft
- supports hybrid queries combining vector and full-text ranking @draft

# storage
- connects to S3 backends via configurable endpoint bucket and credentials @draft

# api
- exposes an HTTP API for namespace upsert delete vector query FTS query and hybrid query @draft
